CSS Tip! ‚ú®

You can create icon sprite animations using the steps() animation-timing function ü§ô

You could use this to create little icon button animations, etc. üòé

But how do you do it? Like this üëá

button img {
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: 0 0;
}

The image is a sprite strip of the frames in the animation. To animate the frames, you do something like this:

[aria-pressed=true] img {
  animation: play 0.5s steps(20) forwards;
}

@ keyframes play {
  to {
    object-position: 100% 0;
  }
}

We are toggling aria-pressed in our scripts to show a pressed state and we can then fire the animation to play our sprite üéâ

